Mauritania Gives Iron License to China Minmetals, SNIM Unit

-- B y   O u d a a   M a r o u f
-- 
2011-04-28T17:00:13Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-28/mauritania-gives-iron-license-to-china-minmetals-snim-unit.html
Mauritania  granted an iron-mining
license to Tazadit Underground Mines Co., a joint venture
between China Minmetals Corp. and state-owned Societe Nationale
Industrielle et Miniere, Agence Mauritanienne d’Information
reported.  It will be the first time a company other than
Mauritanita’s SNIM will be mining iron in the West African
nation, the state-owned press agency reported today, citing a
meeting of the government’s weekly Council of Ministers where
mining deals are awarded.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Oudaa Marouf in Nouakchott via Accra at  ebowers1@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Antony Sguazzin at 
 asguazzin@bloomberg.net . 